weekly_top_story.headline: Federal Judge Orders HHS to Stop Sharing Medicaid Enrollees’ Data with Deportation Officials
weekly_top_story.summary: A federal judge has ordered the health department to stop sharing the personal information of 79 million Medicaid enrollees with deportation officials, impacting privacy and immigration policies related to healthcare.
